Protecting Your Privacy
We use data to make shopping on Amazon and our products better and more convenient for you. Protecting your privacy and the security of your data is and has always been a top priority for Amazon.
Trusting us with your data means that we can show you items inspired by your previous purchases, whether that’s a new line of clothing, a film or TV show, or a great book that was just released. It also means that you don't have to enter your payment and delivery information every time you make an order.
Learn more about how we use your data >
What data does Amazon use?
There are a number of ways you provide us with data, including for example, when you buy something, provide a delivery address, leave a review, listen to a song, or contact us for help.
We use your contact and delivery details to verify your identity as well as to prevent fraud in order to protect your security. In addition, we use your contact and delivery details, content preferences, and shopping history, to provide a better experience and to invent new ways to make things even easier for you in the future.
Learn more about what data we collect and use >
How does Amazon keep data secure?
Any time data moves between your devices or our databases, we encrypt it to keep it secure. Protecting information about our customers is key to our business, and we are not in the business of selling your personal information to others.
Learn more about how we secure your privacy >
How do I view and manage my data on Amazon?
You can access and manage your data, such as your content, order history and communication preferences, in
Your Account
, manage your
digital and device privacy settings
directly on the device you’re using, or manage your
advertising choices
. For further personal information, go to
Request personal information
.
Alternatively, should you wish to Close your Account and Delete your Data, please go to
Request the Closure of Your Account and the Deletion of Your Personal Information
.
Learn more about how to access and manage your information >
